cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR

The paper deals with the application of deep learning techniques for the classification of brain tumors using MRI data. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of transfer learning, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of deep learning models for classification and prediction also falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the visualization of intermediate layer outputs, which falls under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with the use of noninvasive imaging techniques for the diagnosis of brain tumors, which falls under the category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
